        "summary": "This hadith, narrated by Ibn Abbas, describes the Prophet Muhammad's generous custom during Ramadan: he would release all captives and give charity to every person who asked. This reflects the spirit of mercy and generosity that defines the holy month, setting a prophetic example for all Muslims to increase their charitable giving during Ramadan.",
